notesStmt.note: Paper patched, fixed with silk gauze.
Some lacunae supplied by a later hand on different paper (folios 1, 57, 58, 123, 124).
Catalogue of Hebrew Manuscripts in the Gaster Collection, the British Library, London (London: Hebrew Section. Oriental and India Office Collection, 1996).

msContents.summary: Leviticus, Numbers, and Deuteronomy with Targum Onḳelos and Rashi's commentary

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 40; written lines: 40; Number of lines differ from page to page. Pricking or ruling is not visible. Main text is punctuated, commentary in unpunctuated. The layout and the script are both influenced by printed books.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite square and semi-cursive script of the 18th century.

binding.p: In-house, half-bound. Spine: 'Leviticus and Deuteronomy. Hebrew & Aramaic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 9893.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Gaster (b. 1856, d. 1939), scholar and rabbi: his manuscript, Cod. G. 326: inscribed with his name (folios 1r, 2r, 123v); purchased by the British Museum from him on 12 April, 1924: inscribed (back flyleaf [i]v).
